\begin_layout Standard
CTU CAN FD only transmitts a frame after specific moment in time with respect
 to its Time base (see 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "sec:Time-base"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

).
 Moment in time when frame is allowed to be transmitted is configured via
 TIMESTAMP_L_W, TIMESTAMP_U_W words in TXT buffer.
 It is assumed that Time base is up-counting unsigned counter.
 When Time base reaches value stored in TIMESTAMP_L_W, TIMESTAMP_U_W, frame
 stored in TXT buffer is allowed for transmission (assuming that it is in
 highest priority TXT buffer in 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Ready
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 state), as is visualized in Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:time-triggered-transmission"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

.
 Note that this does not mean that CTU CAN FD will transmit the frame immediatel
y, it will still wait until bus is idle.
 If TXT buffer is in 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

Ready
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 state, and Time base counter did not reach moment of transmission yet,
 CTU CAN FD waits until this condition is satisfied.
 If during this time another node on CAN bus starts transmitting a frame,
 CTU CAN FD becomes receiver of such frame.
\end_layout

